The firewater discharge controller.
A collection of functional equipment intended to be used for first aid service in case of emergency.
An arrestor which is a trap over an opening, e.g. of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system.
A specially designed switch with connections for inputs from multiple flame detectors. The switch has a built in logic to determine the presence of a flame based on these inputs.
A system that burns waste in an elevated flame in the open air.

A tank or vessel in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainder heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel.
An orifice plate which restrict the flow and thus develops the differential pressure that is proportional to the square of the flow rate.
A device capable of detecting droplets of water vapour suspended in the air near the ground.
Materials used to transfer loads to the ground and maintain structural stability.
An analyser intended to determine the freezing point of a liquid.
A hollow cone with a tube extending from the smaller end and that is designed to catch and direct a downward flow.
Is an artefact which is necessary, useful or desirable, especially for living or working but is not a tool for production.
A plug capable of being melted and fused.
Galvanic isolation is the principle of isolating functional sections of electric systems so that charge-carrying particles cannot move from one section to another.
An analyser which analyses the composition of gaseous mixture with two or more components.
A static device generating centrifugal force from an incoming flow which separates solid or liquids from a gas of a different density.
A process instrument that records values represented by the input signal(s).
A system that injects grease for lubrication or sealing.
Is a framework of metal bars or wire which is placed in front of something. Often a terminal unit for delivering supply air to a room or for collecting extract air from a room.
An artefact which is intended to wear down, polish, or sharpen by the abrasive action of a high-speed grinding wheel or disc.
An artefact which is an upstanding tapered shaft or rod fixed to a permanent guide base and intended to be used to guide equipment to the seabed.
An electromagnetic storage device, continuously available within a computer system.
A detector capable of detecting both heat and smoke.
An alarm device that makes a loud warning sound.
A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.
A reel capable of holding a hose.
Device used to increase the humidity in air by adding water under pressure as a spray into the air.
A meter intended to measure and indicate and/or produce a signal which represents the measured humidity.
An artefact for releasably connecting hydraulic fluid lines, having means for closing the fluid path when the connector is released.
An arrangement to supply hydraulic power according to specified levels and tolerances.
A device which is intended to initiate a spark that ignites a combustible mixture.
A building or area within a building that is used for activities associated with manufacturing, engineering works and maintenance and is not an office building.
A basic physical and organizational structure or facilities (e.g. buildings and roads) needed for the operation of a site.
A physical object that detects an aspect of something; records, modifies and/or displays such an aspect or performs a combination of these activities.
Which is a structure of related instrumentation and control components intended to perform a measurement, control, actuation, monitoring and/or safeguarding activity.
Is a communication system.
Technology and Infrastructure to manage electronic information handling.
A propeller like device with agitational or rotational movement located in a tank to prevent the content of the tank to build component segments.
An air balancing unit on a nodding donkey.
An artefact intended for central conditioning and pressure increase of ventilation air.
Is an artefact intended to retrieve a material at a particular location and inserted into something so as to test its conditions.
A detecting instrument that is intended to analyse a substance for its composition and/or properties.

An attenuator is a telecommunication device that reduces the amplitude of a signal without appreciably distorting its waveform. Attenuators are usually passive devices. The degree of attenuation may be fixed, continuously adjustable, or incrementally adjustable.
A transmitter measuring an axial displacement and generating a standardized output signal representing the axial measured displacement.
Is a gas flow damper intended to adjust an air flow rate through a duct.
A loading and/or unloading system which is located in water deep enough for a ship to moor.

In woodturning, metalworking, metalspinning, and glassworking, a lathe is a machine tool which spins a block of material so that when abrasive, cutting, or deformation tools are applied to the block, it can be shaped to produce an object which has rotational symmetry about an axis of rotation.
A physical object that detects levels; records, modifies and/or displays or performs a combination of these activities.
An artefact for the rescue of personnel from an installation in the case of an emergency situation.
A facility to give light when the life buoy is in the water.
An artefact which is a raft for emergency situations.
Is a solid or fabricated metal or wooden beam, suspended from a hoist/crane or from a forklift, designed to provide multiple lifting points.
A lifting device also serving as a cover or protection.
A functional unit used to blind off a process stream.
An analyser for liquid.
A detector which is capable of detecting selected types of liquids.
A transducer which produces a signal with a defined relationship to the force applied to it.
A retrievable and configurable device to route and re-route flow true the cap.
An artefact which contains fins or vanes intended to control a flow of air. Typically also to separate water droplets from an air stream.
A level transmitter which uses a floater and magnetic contacts to measure and transmit level.
A manual call point is a device which enables personnel to raise an alarm in the event of a fire incident by pressing a frangible element to activate the alarm system.
A control switch that is operated by a person.
A physical object that is related to the sea or sea transport.
Is a support (item).
An artefact which is a pipeline fitting used to create a rigid pressure containing joint in a pipeline or flowline.
An artefact for the calibration of flow meters.
A microphone, sometimes called a mic (pronounced mike), is a device that converts sound into an electrical signal.
An equipment class that contains classes that not covered by any other parent class.

Short for modulator/demodulator. A communications device that converts one form of a signal to another that is suitable for transmission over communication circuits, typically from digital to analogue and then from analogue to digital.
Is a bracket intended to attach an item to another item.
An analyser giving as output a signal that represents more than one physical properties of the analysed substance.
Is an artefact intended for a number of input channels to share one output channel.
A very accurate flow meter used to record oil exports.
Is a building intended to provide a working space for people and their resources.
A post or buoy placed over a shoal or bank to warn vessels, also a signal mark on land.
Equipment which projects an image on a screen by passing light through a transparent slide or other transparency.
Is a fixed assembly of rails or beams, girders, brackets and framework on which a movable or fixed hoisting mechanism travels.
An artefact which is a collection of artefacts to be managed as one for some purpose.
A facility used to fasten lifting or movement equipment to the structure. A padeye have hole for a shackle.
One-way communications device in which the intended receiver is alerted to receive a message or return a phone call.
A system intended to contact people through a pager. It is pre-date mobile phone technology.
A container that can be attached to a hook for lifting one or more people.
An element designed to measure pH (potential of Hydrogen).
A pressure vessel intended for sending a pig into a pipeline.
A flowloop that allows a pipeline pig to move from one pipe to another.
A pressure vessel intended for receiving a pig from a pipeline.
A transmitter intended to detect a pig passage and transmit a signal representing the measured value.
A facility on a pipeline for inserting and retrieving a scraper or pig.
An artefact which is intended for bending pipes.
A physical object used in or in connection with a piping system.
Is a piping assembly of piping components to be pre-fabricated as one item.

A handheld or fixed device designed to identify and record the location of an object on the earth's surface. GPS, GALILEO, SYLEDIS, HYPERFIX, LORAN-C, DECCA etc. are all brands and working on different networks.
Elements like impellers rotating by the pressure of the fluid  in a closed conduit to measure the flow of a liquid.
A device that removes voltage spikes from an AC or DC electrical supply.

Is a facilty for measure & control, including the main plant computerized operational system, where all process, utility and off site activities are monitored. The system may be located in the main control room. (e.g. PLC Programmable logic controller, DCS distributed control system, ENMC Electrical Network Monitoring and Control system).
Is an alarm system.
A mechanical structure intended to receive a number of pieces of basically standardized modular equipment.
An element intended to determine a level based on high frequency electromagnetic waves.
Is a heat exchanger which cools a fluid and heats the surrounding environment.
A mobile radio communications centre.
A transceiver which has the methods of signalling through space, without connecting wires.
Intended to generate radioactive radiation.
Is a piece of hardware intended to read and decode information encoded on a carrier.
An analyser intended to determine the oxidation and reduction capability of material.

A pressure transmitter where pressure is applied to one side of the sensor while the other side is open to atmosphere. The transmitter generate standardized output signal representing the measured value.

A RTU, or Remote Terminal Unit is a device which interfaces objects in the physical world to a DCS or SCADA system by transmitting telemetry data to the system and/or altering the state of connected objects based on control messages received from the system.
Assigned for living and accommodation.
Is a civil item intended for vehicle traffic.

A router is a computer networking device that forwards data packets toward their destinations through a process known as routing. Routing occurs at layer 3 (Network layer) of the OSI seven-layer model.
Safety barriers are devices that limit the current, voltage, and total energy delivered to a sensor in a hazardous area or flammable environment in order to prevent an explosion.
A sample loop adds a predetermined volume to the process.
A system that provides voice and telefax communication via satellites.
Is a conveyer intended to move dry, solid material from one location to another by means of a helix or screw rotating in a cylindrical conduit.
A manual control switch which has more then two possible positioning states.
A vibrating screen for sifting out rock cuttings from drilling mud.
An equipment class that contains classes that normally are the responsibility of a department for mechanical engineering that are not covered by the mechanical equipment class.
A wheel which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe.
A damper intended for closing off parts of a ventilation system.
A completion component that is used to house gas-lift valves and similar devices that require communication with the annulus.
A detectable transmitted energy (e.g. voltage, current, pneumatic or magnetic field strength) by which information can be transmitted.
A device with one input and at least two outputs used for dividing a detectable transmitted energy (as a voltage, current, or  magnetic field strength) by which information can be transmitted.

A Single buoy mooring (SBM) or Single point mooring (SPM) is a loading buoy anchored offshore that serves as a mooring point and interconnect for tankers loading or offloading gas or fluid products. SBMs are the link between the geostatic subsea manifold connections and the weathervaning tanker. They are capable of handling any size ship, even very large crude carriers (VLCC) where no alternative facility is available.
A large basin with taps that supplies water.
Device which separates oil from water by mechanically wipe the oil of the water surface.
A block through which a rope can be reeved without access to an end.
Is a software intended to describe a process step in a computer language. Typically a software implementation of a control function.
An analyser intended to determine a mixture of solid particles in liquids or solid or liquid droplets in air.
A detector intended to detect sand in a fluid.
A device decreasing noise in a HVAC system.
A meter intended to measure a sound pressure level.
A device which removes incandescent particles from a gas stream. Spark arrestors are fitted to vehicles and stationary engines which are operated in potentially flammable atmospheres.
A device that is made as a tool to be used for a special purpose.
An analyser intended to determine specific gravity's of materials. Typically of liquids.
A beam that is used to spread ropes or slings when lifting.
Is a support (item) intended to carry the load of piping components.
Is a support structure intended to support a flare or vent pipe.
A mechanical device capable of reducing the stroke length of a pump.
Is an artefact intended to collect a heavy phase by making use of gravity.
An artefact joining two parts so that one or both can pivot freely (as on a bolt or pin).
A device that transfer data between a computer and a magnetic tape.
A physical object that detects temperatures; records, modifies and/or displays or performs a combination of these activities.
An element which uses the principle of thermal conductivity to measure volume flow rate.
A velocity flow meter which uses the principle of thermal conductivity to measure volume flow rate.

A device that is a mechanical implement for working upon something, as by cutting, striking, rubbing or other processes, in any manual art or industry; usually, one held in and operated by the hand (or fixed in position, as in a lath), but also including certain simple machines, as the lathe; sometimes extended to simple instruments of other kinds.
Is a vehicle which is nonautomotive and is designed to be hauled by road.
A transmitter specially designed to convert the signal in a turbine meter into a standardized output signal.
A flow transmitter providing electrical outputs that are proportional to the flow inputs from an ultrasonic flow meter.
An element intended to determine a level based on  ultrasonic sound waves.
An assembly of hydraulic hoses which can also include electrical cables or optic fibres, used to control a sub sea structure or remote operated vehicle from a platform or a vessel.
Is a sterilizer intended to make use of ultraviolet light.
An analyser intended to determine a vapor pressure.
A switch intended to give a on/off signal when vibration level have reached a pre-set value.
A signal converter intended to convert one video signal type to another video signal type.
A facility with the capability of receiving  video signals and displaying pictures.
A transmitter which output is relative to a measured voltage.
A transmitter specially designed to convert the signal in a vortex flow meter into a standardized output signal.
A compactor is a machine or mechanism used to reduce the size of waste material.
A water cooler is a device that cools and dispenses water.
Is a fresh water system.
A device for producing drinking water, but not necessarily by reverse osmosis.

A well is a collection of (zero or more) holes drilled into the Earth for the purpose of either (1) finding or producing underground resources; or (2) providing services related to the production of underground resources.

The wellhead is assembled from, or incorporates facilities for, the upper casing and tubing hangers. This effectively provides the upper termination of the wellbore and provides a mounting position for the surface flow-control equipment or Christmas tree.
A powerful machine with one or more drums on which to coil a rope, cable, or chain for hauling or hoisting.
A detecting instrument for recording wind speed, and possibly wind direction.
A hoist utilizing a wire-rope for suspending load. Wire hoists are normally electrically powered, but also (hand) lever types exists.
Is a well services facility intended to handle wire lines.
A sling for enclosing material to be hoisted by a tackle or crane made by wire.

A wireless access point (WAP) is a device that allows wired communication devices to connect to a wireless network using Wi-Fi, Bluetooth or related standards. The WAP usually connects to a router, and can relay data between the wireless devices (such as computers or printers) and wired devices on the network.
A device that damps, typically a valve or plate (as in the flue of a furnace) for regulating the draft, or a device to stop vibration, typically a shock absorber or snubber.
A device which gives a visual indication of a measured value.
A valve that is intended for subsurface control/check operation.
A self operating valve that is set to open at a certain pressure level to prevent the pressure in a container or system from reaching unsafe levels.
A container intended to store liquid or solid material partly or totally below grade and that is typically open.
A container that has a characteristic shape and that is made of material with an open structure.
A physical object that is a hood or covering for the top or end of something.
A physical object that is an enclosed space.
A physical object that is an opening in a barrier and a removable physical object that can block the opening.
A physical object that separates enclosed physical objects from those outside.
A physical object that is a projecting flat rim, plate, collar or rib.
A physical object that is an open structure of beams or bars.
A seal that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other.
An enclosure that also provides support.
A physical object that contains a chamber with several openings.
A physical object intended to reduce or prevent the passage of fluid through an opening.
An equipment class that contains classes of artefacts which is electrical equipment.
An artefact class that contains classes of artefacts or physical resources required for a purpose.
An equipment class that contains heat transfer equipment items with a purpose related to combustion.

CFIHOS name: health, safety and environment equipment class
CFIHOS description: An equipment class that contains classes of artefacts intended to be used to provide health and safety and to prevent environmental hazards.
An equipment class that contains classes that normally are the responsibility of a department for mechanical engineering.
A physical object for storing energy, and which after discharge may be recharged.
A physical object for increasing the power of a signal.
A physical object that is capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from the medium of lower conductivity.
A direct current power supply unit intended to supply stabilised DC electric power according to specified levels and tolerances.
A direct current power supply unit for charging batteries.
An electrical conductor that is of low-impedance, to which several electric circuits can be connected at separate points.
A physical object that is a reel on to which cable is wound during manufacture, for storage, transportation and installation.
A physical object that is a number of capacitor units connected so as to act together.
A mechanical switching device that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current.
A timepiece for the measurement of time.
A transmitter that is intended to measure and transmit conductivity.

A mechanical switching device having only one position of rest, operated otherwise than by hand, capable of making, carrying and breaking currents under normal circuit conditions including operating overload conditions.
An instrument panel containing a set of indicating devices and control units required for operation of a system or part of it.
A transmitter that transmits an analogue electrical current.
A switchgear and controlgear that is an insulated  panel carrying terminals, fuses, etc, for controlling a number of subsidiary electrical circuits.
An electrical conductor that is a busbar used for earthing.
An electrode, which is the conductive part, that can be embedded in a specific conductive medium, e.g. concrete or coke, in electric contact with the Earth.
A detector intended to detect a leakage current to earth.
An electrode that is an earth electrode consisting of a metal plate buried in the ground.
An electrical conductor that is used to connect the earthing system to structure.
An actuator that produces a specified movement when excited by an electric signal.
An electric accumulator that comprises one or more cells fitted with devices necessary for use, for example case, terminals, marking and protective devices.
An energy transducer that transforms non-electric energy into electric energy.
A heater in which electric energy is converted into heat for useful purposes.
An electric machine for transforming electric energy into mechanical energy.
A starter in which the force for closing the main contacts is provided exclusively by electrical energy.
An electrical connector in which the terminals of an electricity supply are inside holes made to receive the pins of a plug.
An electronic ac converter for changing the frequency.
An electronic converter that changes direct electric current to single-phase or polyphase alternating currents.
A projector providing a beam of intense illumination.

A physical object that by the fusing of one or more of its specially designed and proportioned components, opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time.
An electric cable, that is also an electric heater, with or without a shield or a metallic sheath, intended to give off heat for heating purposes.
An electrical filter having a single pass-band extending from a specified cut-off frequency upwards.
A physical object that makes the operation of a piece of equipment dependent upon the condition, position or operation of one or more other pieces of equipment.
A physical object that isolates.
A physical object that is a closed, rigid box or casing used to enclose and protect the junctions of electric wires or cables.
A physical object intended to produce an optical radiation, usually visible.
An electrical filter having a single pass-band extending from zero frequency to a specified cut-off frequency.
A physical object that is an electric light and its fittings.
An electric cable intended for transmission of electric power.
A physical object intended to supply electric power according to specified levels and tolerances.

A transformer that, by electromagnetic induction, transforms a system of alternating voltage and current into another system of voltage and current usually of different values and at the same frequency for the purpose of transmitting electrical power.
An electric converter for converting an alternating current into a direct current.
A physical object that can be any electrical device, usually incorporating an electromagnet, whereby a current or signal in one circuit can open or close another circuit.
An electric cable intended for  transmission of electric signals.
An electromagnetic coil, which is a cylindrical coil, the length of which is much greater than its transverse dimensions and which is used to produce a magnetic field.
A switchgear and controlgear bearing a set of switches for connecting and disconnecting the various circuits of an electrical system, as of a telegraph, telephone, etc.

A physical object that is a general term covering switching devices and their combination with associated control, measuring, protective and regulating equipment, also assemblies of such devices and equipment with associated interconnections, accessories, enclosures and supporting structures.

A physical object that converts sound signals into corresponding variations of electric current (or potential), which is transmitted by wire or radio to a distant point where it is reconverted into sound.
A detector intended to detect temperature.

A pilot switch whose function is controlled by variations of temperature and whose contacts make or break automatically a load circuit when the temperature of the ambient space in which its sensing element placed or the temperature of the surface on which it is fixed reaches a predetermined value.

A semiconductor device that is a three-terminal semiconductor rectifier made up of four layers, p-n-p-n, so that when the fourth is positive with respect to the first, a voltage pulse applied to the third layer initiates a flow of current through the device which continues as long as it is greater than some minimum value.
A pilot switch intended to create a switch action at a pre-set value.
An ac power supply unit that maintains a continuous supply of electric power to the equipment it protects.
A physical object that consists of an electric motor and controller that is used to adjust the motor's operating speed.
A transmitter of which the output is proportional to a measured vibration.
A transmitter for weighing large quantities of material, and of which the output is proportional to the measured weight.
A physical object for arc welding, either ac or dc, comprising a supply unit and a regulator.
A physical object that is intended to bring air to a specified quality.
A cooler that is intended to use air as the cooling medium.
An indirect contact heat exchanger that is intended to heat a liquid.
A cooler that is intended to change a vapour to liquid.
A heat exchanger that is intended to cool a physical object.
A cooler and an air cooled heat exchanger that is a tall structure through which air circulates by convection.
A drier is a physical object that is intended to remove absorbed or adsorbed liquid or water vapour below saturation state.
A burner that burns gas emitted from a process into the atmosphere.
A physical object that is intended to transfer heat from one object to another.
A furnace that is intended for the combustion of waste material.
A pressure transmitter where pressure is applied to one side of the sensor while the other side has a vacuum chamber.
An electromagnetic transducer that is a physical object made of conducting material which is capable of radiating or receiving electromagnetic waves.
A detecting element that is intended to detect axial displacement.

A physical object that is a hollow body with a flared mouth made of cast metal. Formed to emit a clear musical sound by the sonorous vibration of its entire circumference when struck by a clapper, hammer or other appliance.
A detecting element that is intended to detect changes in the dielectric constant.
An analysing instrument that is intended to determine the cloud point of a fluid.

A physical object that can store data and program(s) that operates on the data. A general purpose computer can be programmed to solve any reasonable problem expressed in logical and arithmetical terms.
A detecting element or probe that is used with a conductivity meter to measure the conductivity of a liquid.
A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a conductivity meter.
A terminal box that is used as accommodation for control function circuits.
A mass flow meter that uses the Coriolis principle to measure a mass flow rate through the meter.
A detecting instrument intended to measure, indicate and/or produce a signal which represents the rate or degree of corrosion.
A detecting element that is a piece of suitable metal meant to corrode and give an indication of the corrosion rate.
A detecting instrument that counts, especially an electronic or mechanical device that automatically counts occurrences or repetitions of phenomena or events.
A signal converter that is intended to convert one current signal to another current signal.
A signal converter that is intended to convert an analogue signal (4 - 20 mA) to a proportional linear pneumatic output signal.
A signal converter that is intended to convert a current input signal to a proportional voltage output signal.
An analysing instrument intended to determine the density of a substance.
An analysing instrument intended to determine the dew point of a substance.
A gauge that is intended for measuring and indicating pressure differences.
A level transmitter that is measuring liquid level by sensing pressure difference between two points, e.g. the hydrostatic pressure at the bottom of a tank to the atmosphere pressure.
A pilot switch intended to switch or give an on/off signal when the measured differential pressure has reached a pre-set value.
A pressure transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received pressure difference signal.
Connecting with a coupling or coupler.
A flow transmitter that is specially designed to convert the signals from an electromagnetic flow meter into a standardized electrical output signal.
A controller that uses in-built algorithms executed by electronic circuitry to perform its function.
A detector that is intended to sense a flame.
An analysing instrument intended to determine the flash point of a substance.
A gauge intended to indicate a liquid or gas flow.
A regulator that normally use the differential pressure principle across an orifice to control the valve trim and regulate flow.
A functional switch that is intended to give a signal when the flow have reached a pre-set value.
A signal converter that is intended to convert a frequency or rotational speed input signal into a 0 - 20 mA or 4 - 20 mA current output signal.
A detector that is intended to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas.
An actuator intended to be operated by hydraulic power.
A controller that is designed or can be programmed to operate and control hydraulic operated systems.
A control panel with an array of systematically arranged (piano like) keys by which a machine is operated or by which an instrument can be played on.
An electroacoustic transducer that converts an electric signal into sound.
A level gauge that use a float containing a magnet to transfer information about its position to a indicator rail with white and red flaps mounted on the outside of the tube.
A mechanical controller that is intended to position a given item in accordance with a received input signal.
An analysing instrument intended to measure, indicate and/or produce a signal which represents the measured alkalinity / acidity in a fluid or matter.
A detector that is intended to detect a pig inside the pipeline or pig receiver.

A fluid sensor producing a differential pressure by means of two straigth tubes mounted in line with the direction of the fluid movement. One tube is open-ended and measures the stagnation pressure of the fluid. The other tube is closed in front but has openings along the tube to measure the static pressure of the fluid.
An actuator that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power.
A mechanical controller that is using pneumatic components to execute its function.
A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a position detector.
A flow transmitter specially designed to convert the signal from a positive displacement flow meter into a standardized electrical output signal.
An analysing instrument intended to determine the pour point of a fluid, i.e. the lowest temperature at which an oil or other liquid will pour under given conditions.
A gauge intended to measure and display a representation of a measured pressure.
A regulator that is controlling/regulating the pressure in a system.
A functional switch that (usually) turns an electrical circuit on or off when the pressure level reaches a pre-set value.
A signal converter that is intended to convert a pressure input signal to DC output signal.
A physical object that produces characters or graphic symbols on paper or other medium.
A detecting element that is intended to sense proximity.
A position switch that is operated without mechanical contact with the moving part.
A manual control switch that is intended to switch when you push or touch the button.
A level transmitter that is producing a standardized electrical output signal based on the input signal from a radar type level sensor.
A level transmitter that is producing a standardized electrical output signal based on the input signal from radioactive level measurements.
A process instrument that records values represented by the input signal(s).

A temperature sensing element that operate on the principle of changes in electrical resistance of pure metals (sintered semiconductor material) and are characterized by an almost linear positive change in resistance with temperature.
An orifice plate that is intended for use as a restrictor.
A variable area flow meter which consists of a tapered tube of glass with a float inside that is pushed up by flow and pulled down by gravity.
A physical object that is a pressure relieving device designed to burst at a calibrated pressure to prevent pressure in systems or vessels from reaching unsafe levels.
A physical object intended to be used to collect and contain representative specimens or selections.
A tank gauge that is intended to intermittently lower a displacer to measure a liquid level, bottom level, interface level or density.
A detector that is intended to sense smoke.
A detecting instrument that is intended to measure the upload and download speed of an internet connection.
A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a rotational speed sensor.
A gauge that is intended to measure and indicate a temperature.
A regulator that is intended to keep a temperature within certain boundaries.
A functional switch that is intended to give an on or off signal when the temperature have reached a pre-set value.
A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a temperature element.
An analysing instrument that is intended to determine a physical property that is named thermal conductivity.

A pair of electrical conductors of dissimilar materials, joined at one end (the measuring or hot junction), which produces an electromotive force (e.m.f.) due to the Seebeck effect in a circuit formed by connecting the other ends of the dissimilar materials used (the reference or cold junction) to a device for measuring e.m.f.  Def. acc. to IEC 902 1987.

A physical object that is a pressure-tight receptacle adapted to receive a temperature sensing element, provided with external threads or other means for pressure-tight attachment to a vessel or pipe.
A timepiece that measures a time interval and signals its end; a time-switch.
A transceiver that transmits a signal automatically in response to an appropriate triggering signal.
A velocity flow meter that uses a multi bladed rotor to measure fluid flow rate in units of volumetric flow through a closed conduit.

A velocity flow meter that measures the velocity of a flow by measuring the time difference between an ultrasonic pulse sent in the flow direction and an ultrasound pulse sent opposite the flow direction.
A level transmitter that is using ultrasonic sound to continuously monitor the level of a liquid or particulate matter in a tank or vessel.
A differential pressure flow meter that uses a v-cone as the restriction body in the flow stream.
A pipe or tube that has a constriction with a relative long passage with a smooth coned entry and exit.
A detecting element that is intended to sense mechanical vibration and in which the oscillating motion is transferred into a voltage or current signal.
A recording instrument that is recording signals originated by a TV camera on a moving magnetic tape for subsequent reproduction or transmission.
An analysing instrument intended to determine the viscosity of a fluid.
A signal converter that is intended for converting an input voltage signal into an output current signal.
A flow meter that measures the velocity of a fluid in a pipe by detecting the frequency of vortices being shed from a specially shaped obstructing element in the fluid stream.
A detecting element that can be the sensing element of an anemometer or wind gauge.
An analysing instrument intended to determine the wobble index of a gas.

A physical object that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.
A physical object that has a protruding part through which a stream of fluid is directed.
A physical object that is a long tube or hollow body intended for conduction of liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials, or used for structural purposes.
A physical object that is used to change piping direction with a non-standard radius.
A physical object that is a circular plate with no central opening and holes to match mating flanged ends. It is also equipped with a handle.
A physical object that has three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees.
A fluid conductor that consists of pipe, possibly also including pumps, valves, and control devices, intended for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids.
A bellows that is a flexible corrugated tubular element providing axial and radial flexibility and pressure containment.
A physical object that is a vertical or near vertical pipe for the upward flow of liquid or gas.
A physical object that consists of two discs with equal thickness and outer diameter connected with a flat bar. One of the discs has a hole, while the other disc is without hole.
A physical object which is a short section of pipe used to connect ends of pipes/pipelines.
A trap that consists of a chamber into which condensed steam from steam pipes etc. is allowed to drain, and which automatically ejects it without permitting the escape of steam.
A filter that is separating solid particles from a fluid by passing the fluid through a wire mesh, screen or metal plates containing perforations or slits.
A well string hanger that is used for production tubing. The tubing hanger incorporates a sealing system to ensure that the tubing conduit and annulus are hydraulically isolated.
A resistance through which the neutral pint of a supply system is earthed, in order to limit the current that flows on the occurrence of an earth fault.
A physical object intended to hold an object firmly.
A physical object intended to prevent something to pass.
A physical object designed to eject agents, e.g. water or a chemical, to put out fires.
A shower intended for emergency situations.
A physical object intended to reduce a noise level.
A physical object that supplies and mixes air to a liquid or solids.
A dynamic compressor in which the gas is accelerated by the action of a bladed rotor and where the main flow is along the rotation axis of the rotor.
A physical object intended to support and locate a moving or static element and capable of reducing friction and transfer forces in a connection.
A physical object intended to compress and supply air or gas at medium pressure and medium volume flow.
A physical object intended to arrest or prevent the motion of an item. Typically by means of friction.
A dynamic compressor in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial.
A dynamic pump that contains impellers provided with vanes to generate centrifugal force to achieve the required pressure head.
A physical object that uses centrifugal force to separate phases of different densities.
A transmission that is intended to transmit energy between two shafts providing the capability to connect and disconnect the shafts.
A physical object that is driven by a prime mover by which energy is either constantly or periodically added to an amount of gas in order to increase its pressure.
An internal combustion engine in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge.
A physical object that contains a diverging channel-shaped chamber in which part of the kinetic energy of the fluid is converted into pressure energy.
A physical object that provides rotational or reciprocating energy to driven equipment.
A physical object that is intended to form material by forcing it in liquid phase through a shaping die by applying pressure and fix the form in the solid phase.
A physical object that is intended to deliver or exhaust volumes of vapour or gas at low differential pressure.
An internal combustion engine that is a reciprocating engine in which gaseous fuel is mixed with air to form a combustible mixture in a cylinder which is fired by spark ignition.

A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.
A physical object that is a casing with an arrangement of two or more gear-wheels transmitting rotating motion from the input shaft to the output shaft.
An enclosure intended to protect equipment from weather influences or to protect surroundings of equipment from equipment noise.
A cylinder where the piston is actuated by pressurized hydraulic fluid.
A motor that is intended to generate power by means of high pressure oil.
A system that provides lubricant to rotating or moving items.

A seal that comprises of a set of one or more rotating and stationary seal faces, together with auxiliary hardware, separated by a film of fluid intended to reduce flow loss around a rotating shaft to an acceptable level.

A physical object intended to be used for fluid mixing processes typically a rotating piece of equipment comprised of a driver such as a motor which rotates an agitator immersed in the fluid(s) that need to be mixed.
An internal combustion engine that is an induction compression ignition exhaust engine which ignites a petrol air mixture with an electric spark.
A motor that is driven by compressed gas. Typically air.

A pressure vessel located in both pump- and compressor piping systems in order to reduce residual pulsation fluctuations, as a result of discontinue operation effects, within an allowable level specified.
A physical object that adds or removes mechanical energy to a fluid, either constantly or periodically.
A positive displacement compressor in which forced reduction of gas volume takes place by the movement of a displacing element in a cylinder or enclosure.
A positive displacement compressor in which compression displacement is effected by the positive action of rotating elements.
A physical object that is intended to keep other physical objects at a predefined distance and hence having a spacer function.
A thermodynamic turbine in which steam is made to do work by expanding so as to create kinetic energy by acting on moving blades attached to a disc or drum.
A fluid coupling intended to allow a smooth start of a driven equipment and then keeping a nearly constant speed.

An expander of the turbine type used to reduce the pressure of a gas flow by leading it through a turbine rotor by which the recovered energy is transferred into rotational energy for either power generation or mechanical drive application.
A physical object that is an arched device intended to embrace two parts to hold or unite them in position, or to divide loads.
A conveyor that consists of a suitably tensioned endless belt made from hard wearing materials and arranged to run over rollers.
A conveyor in which endless chains are used to support slats, apron, pans, buckets, as distinct from the use of single band.
A physical object for moving articles or bulk material from place to place (as by an endless moving belt or a chain of receptacles).
A physical object that is an instrument, machine, machine part, or tool that cuts.
A closed transport device that is a gathering line tied into a trunk line.
A vehicle with power operated prongs that can be raised and lowered by will, for loading, transporting and unloading goods; chiefly used in factories and warehouses.
A physical object that applies force for pressing by using fluid pressure for force multiplication.

A conveyor comprising a series of closely spaced rollers set so that their crests can support articles to be conveyed. They may be power-driven, or freely revolving. Tapered rollers are used to form bends in the conveyor line.
A conveyor consisting of a series of slats generally made of metal or wood  attached to an endless chain.
A support that is a large and straight piece of normally timber or iron forming one of the main structural member of a building or supporting structure.
A gravity separator where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.
A physical object intended to catch fluid droplets.
A separator intended to separate material from a solution or suspension by electrostatic charge.
A separator intended to remove solids from vapour or liquid.
A filter element intended to collect particles from a stream in a filter or strainer.
A distributor intended to distribute or redistribute a vapour.
A trough that is located along the eaves to catch and carry liquid.
A hatch door used to provide and secure access into a void, vessel or riser. To enable maintenance or inspection.
A cyclone separator intended to separate a fluid by hydraulic forces.
A physical object intended to provide access to a certain part or level of equipment, and that consists of rungs between two profiles.
A physical object intended to lift or to enable lifting equipment or a part of equipment.
A lug with a hole for a lifting hook intended to lift the item or a part of it.
A support intended to support one or more pipes.
A vertical vessel intended to enable chemical reactions or physical processes utilising differences in density of fluids and/or forced flow of fluid.
A physical object intended to mechanically remove a deposit from a surface.

A distillation column intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles.
A physical object that is a layer or surface with a shape in two dimensions and length in the third dimension surrounding a space. Typically the cylindrical part of a vessel.
A catcher intended to catch and separate liquid slugs from a fluid stream.
A distillation column intended to remove light components from a fluid.

A vessel intended to contain fluid for storage. Typically a receiving or collecting function for further distribution. Typically with a vertical and cylindrical or square shape and a flat or conical bottom.
A container intended for storage and/or processing of fluids.
A physical object that is a floating object made for various purposes.
A mechanical cable that consist of series of interconnected links forming a flexible cable, used for sustaining a tensile load.
A lifting appliance that is a tower or derrick equipped with cables and pulleys that can lift or lower and move loads in multiple directions.
A lift that has a chamber or compartment for moving personnel or goods.
A physical object that is a body intended to protect as a cushion (as a foam rubber or a wood float) between a boat and a dock or between two boats that lessens shocks and prevents chafing.
A deck that is intended to provide a landing and take-off capability for helicopters.
A boat that is intended to rescue people in an emergency case.
A physical object that is designed to load or unload products into or from vehicles, wagons or vessels at variable positions.
A mechanical cable that is a large stout cord of strands of fibres twisted or braided together.
A vehicle that is intended for transporting heavy loads.
An motor vehicle that is long, low and open intended for carrying goods by road.
A physical object that is any conveyance (usually wheel, e.g. a cart, lorry, motorcar, but also a sledge) for goods or passengers on land.
A physical object for changing a signal into a corresponding movement.
An automatic tracking system used on ships and by vessel traffic services (VTS) for identifying and locating vessels.
A wall that is designed to retain its integrity against a defined blast loading and fire that may subsequently follow.
A structure to control the formation of lateral buckles along a pipeline or flowline.

A constructed retaining wall around storage where potentially polluting substances are handled, processed or stored, for the purposes of containing any unintended escape of material from that area until such time as remedial action can be taken.
A physical object that is an assembly of busbar, bus duct enclosure, busbar insulation mounts etc.

An instrument that indicates either a) magnetic bearings by alignment of its needle on the magnetic poles, or b) reference bearing by radio signal, or c) change of orientation in relation to a gyromaintained line.
An artefact that is used to control fibrillation of the heart.
A 'device' that is providing diversion of something from an expected course or direction.
A physical object that provides reactance in a circuit.
A switch that turns electrical current on and/or off.
A radio beacon in the mobile service the emissions of which are intended to facilitate search and rescue operations (EPIRB).
A wall which is also a fire divider.
A large sheet-metal duct or casing through which air is passed for forced-draught, ventilation or air-conditioning purposes.
Intended to inject material. Typically it consists of a pipe connected to an item and a valve in the pipe.
A lifting device, usually portable, for lifting heavy weights by force acting from below; in the commonest form, having a rack and a pinion wheel or screw and a handle turned by hand.
A switchgear and controlgear that houses motor starters to control electric motors.
A gas flow damper that is used to relieve built-up pressure in a duct system to prevent damage to HVAC equipment.

A physical object for detecting the presence of objects at a distance, or ascertaining their position or motion, by transmitting short radio waves and detecting or measuring their return after being reflected.
A radio transmitter, usually non-directional, that emits identifiable signals intended for radio direction-finding.
A tool that can be used to install or remove machines or equipment.
A ring of conducting material which is attached to and rotates with a shaft, so that the electric current may be transferred to a stationary circuit through a fixed brush pressing against it.
A physical object that is intended to mix fluid by means of diverging the flow with static obstacles or by increasing locally the velocity.
A physical object that includes a water jet or propeller used on vessels intended to provide a means to move the vessel sideways for maintaining the vessel's position without anchors.
Which is flat and typically vertical suitable for separation.
A physical object that is intended for water transport.
A relief valve that is used for pressure compensation purposes by admitting (letting in) a pressure to prevent that vacuum is forming when filling or emptying a system.
A valve that can be used for rapid depressurizing of a high pressure system.
A valve that permits fluid to flow in one direction only.
A device compensating for axial or radial movement between two elements that is connected.

A valve that can be used to modify (regulate) the fluid flow rate in a process control system. It usually includes an actuator, which responds to a signal from the controlling system and changes the position of the flow controlling element in the valve.
A control valve that is intended to operate at high temperature, and admit water into a deluge system.

A physical object that is an assembly of a sensing element and necessary ancillary devices making it able of detecting a state, e.g. pressure, temperature, or detect the presence of a selected substance, and produce a signal based on the detection.
A physical object that comprises a printed circuit board with electronic components intended for receive, process/transform and transmit electrical signals.
A valve that is assigned to act in case of emergency.
A flow transmitter providing an output signal that is proportional to the flow inputs from a flow element.
An 'equipment class' that is a class of devices whose members normally is a part of the outfitting of a galley.
A connector intended for hose connection.
A transmitter that produces a continuous standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a level sensor.
A data communication system intended for communication between parties in a restricted area.
An access point that is of sufficient size to allow a person to safely enter a vessel, space, chamber or drain.
A valve that is regulated with hand power.
A gas flow damper that prevents back flow in a duct.
Physical access control equipment and/or systems intended to regulate or control entry into and/or exit from a controlled area, protected area or a restricted area.
A fluid regulator that relieves pressure from an enclosed space when the pressure reaches a predetermined value.
A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a pressure element.
A nozzle intended to enable transfer of process material.
A support connecting a riser to a structure.
A nozzle where liquid is introduced under pressure.
In a communications network, a network node equipped for interfacing with another network that uses different protocols.
An 'artefact' intended for the termination of cables.
A fluid regulator that can be used to control (i.e. permit, obstruct, regulate or divert) a fluid stream.
A physical object that is an element that receives a process variable signal from a sensor and converts it into an output signal.
A totalizer that adds up flow measurements.
An electric signal transducer that is intended to convert one type of standardized transmission signal into another.
A physical object that is a thin plate with a specified hole in the middle. It is usually placed in a pipe to measure the rate of fluid flow.
A physical object that is the primary element of a measuring chain which converts the input variable into a signal suitable for measurement.

A regulator that operates automatically to affect a controlled variable by comparing the value of the controlled variable with the value of a reference variable in order to reduce the difference between them.
Equipment intended to enable the drilling of holes. Typically in the earth for oil and/or gas production.

A Bell nipple is a section of large diameter pipe fitted to the top of the blowout preventers that the flow line attaches to via a side outlet, to allow the drilling fluid to flow back over the shale shakers to the mud tanks. Also an enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well.

A rigid metal conduit that provides the high-pressure pathway for drilling mud to travel approximately one-third of the way up the derrick, where it connects to a flexible high-pressure hose (kelly hose).
A device that is designed for easy washing and dope application of drill pipe threads and collar threads.
A detecting element that is producing a signal that is proportional to a flow rate.
A detecting element that is intended to determine a level.
A detecting element intended to sense pressure.
A detecting element intended to sense temperature.
A detecting instrument that is used for measuring or testing.
A switch intended to switch or give an on/off signal when the measured variable has reached a pre-set value.
A functional switch that is intended to give an on/off signal when particulate material or fluid level have reached a pre-set value.
A pilot switch the actuating system of which is operated by a moving part of a machine, when this part reaches a predetermined position.
An artefact where hydraulics, chemicals, electrical power and signals are distributed from the main umbilicals to different subsea systems.

An integral part of the drilling process, iron roughnecks connect and disconnect drill pipe. Whether pipe is being fed into the wellbore or it is being taken out, the iron roughneck uses a rotary table and torque wrench(es) to make up or break down pipe.
A valve that has linear action which is fitted with a solenoid for quick operation.
A valve that includes a means of operation (e.g. spring / gravity / fluid pressure / counter balance), and is not depending on an external source of energy.
An internal combustion engine that is an induction compression ignition exhaust engine which ignites a fuel air mixture.
A device that generates rotational kinetic energy.
A physical object that is intended to rotate within a fluid and to transform energy within a fluid into mechanical power.
A 'detector' for measuring the velocity, mass, charge, flight direction, and number of dust particles in space.
A gauge that is intended to display a representation of a measured level.
A flow meter for the metering a mixture of two or more fluid phases.
A mist detector that is intended to detect oil mist.
A switch intended to give a on/off signal when the speed have reached a pre-set value.
A drum intended to separate relatively small quantities of liquid from a vapour stream.
A 'device' intended to separate different types of substances.
An 'equipment class' that is a class whose members are used in conjunction with subsea or subaquatic installations and/or operations.
Subsea equipment class that contains classes of artefacts which are infrastructure equipment.
Subsea or subaquatic equipment class that contains classes of artefacts which are instrumentation equipment.
Device or remotely operated tool deployed by an intervention system to mate or interface with an intervention fixture.
Subsea or subaquatic equipment class that contains classes of artefacts which are mechanical equipment.
Subsea infrastructure class that contains classes of artefacts which are structures.
A device that is made as a tool to be used for a subsea or subaquatic purpose.
An injection system which provides service for injection of inhibitors etc. into the process. Serves as utility for make-up purposes of water, products and when required by process.
Flying Leads are used to link connections between subsea structures such as manifolds, trees, Umbilical Termination Units and Subsea Distribution Units.
A functional unit which is consisting of a bottom founded framework structure with three or more legs.
Structure used to support and restrain flexible risers.
A piping system that is situated within the frame and distributes purge gas inside the frame.
Container in which the sample is collected, stored, and transported to the analytical equipment.
A wear bushing that is run into and set in the wellhead or christmas tree to protect the inside wall against wear from the drill bit and drill pipe during drilling operations.

CFIHOS name: subsea distributed temperature sensing fiber optic pod
CFIHOS description: A 'fibre optic pod' for use in a Distributed Temperature Sensing (DTS) system.
Flexible pipe, wholly or in part, resting on the seafloor or buried below the seafloor, and used in a static application.
Tools or devices that enable the installation and/or retrieval of a subsea casing hanger.
Assembly used to attach umbilicals to host structure.

System that controls and monitors the deployment, the operation and the retrieval of subsea production equipment and is used during installation, workover, and intervention of a single subsea tree from a moored or dynamically positioned deepwater mobile offshore drilling unit (MODU) or multi-service vessel (MSV).
An artefact for connecting a well or a manifold to a subsea flowline.
A frame that is a structural framework to provide strength and protection for a subsea manifold.
A device intended to prevent excessive jacket penetration into the soil.
A pipeline crossing which is subsea and located above or below a specific object or geographic feature.
The protection structure that covers the subsea equipment (template, manifold, trees, etc. ) to protect the equipment from third party damages as e.g. dropped objects, anchors or trawl equipment.
Dedicated, unmanned, subsea or subaquatic tools used for installation and inspection, maintenance, and repair (IMR) tasks that require a handling capacity beyond that of free-swimming ROV systems.
A submarine or subaquatic ROV which is a nearly neutral buoyancy submarine that is manipulated from a surface platform by an umbilical.
An umbilical for subsea or subaquatic use between a surface platform and subaquatic equipment or installation.
A termination head for a umbilical, having means for aligning fluid, electrical and optical lines to a mating assembly.
An isolator that isolates electrical conductors.
A measuring relay that, either solely or in combination with other relays, is a constituent of a protection equipment.
A physical object that is a totally sealed, gas-insulated compact switchgear unit. The primary switching devices can be either switch disconnectors or fused switch disconnectors or circuit breakers.
A corrosion protection system using sacrificial anodes or impressed current anodes offering material and giving protection to carbon and low-alloy steel equipment or structures.
A physical object that is automatic and designed to initiate the operation of circuit-breakers and/or disconnectors in a substation according to a specific programme.
A physical object that is protecting against a large but momentary increase in the voltage of an electric circuit.
A physical object that stores electricity during part of an operation.
A connector for holding two parts of a conductor in intimate contact.
An electrical conductor that has several power distribution points.
A control module that is used to control a subsea production system.
A subsea fixed structure supporting a wellhead.
An operated valve that is opened and closed with a motor.

A shear valve is a ram-type BOP, similar in operation to a gate valve, but uses a pair of opposing steel plungers, rams. The rams extend toward the centre of the wellbore to restrict flow or retract open in order to permit flow.
A panel and a photovoltaic module whose main parts are solar cells.

An artefact and a cooling appliance comprising a thermally insulated compartment and a heat pump-chemical or mechanical means-to transfer heat from it to the external environment, cooling the contents to a temperature below ambient.
Intended to measure quantities of absorbed or evolved heat or to determine specific heats.
A device that generates an electrical signal of a specified frequency.
An acoustic device producing a loud sound as a signal or warning.

An instrument transformer in which the secondary current, in normal conditions of use, is substantially proportional to the primary current and differs in phase from it by an angle which is approximately zero for an appropriate direction of the connections.

An instrument transformer in which the secondary voltage, in normal conditions of use, is substantially proportional to the primary voltage and differs in phase from it by an angle which is approximately zero for an appropriate direction of the connections.
A physical object that is intended to process and annunciate alarms.
A computer that is specially designed and programme to calculate flow and to correct for external influence.
A physical object that is transparent and intended for viewing a vessel or piping system interior.
A detecting element that is intended to sense rotational speed.
A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a corrosion sensor.
A heat exchanger using plates as the device for separating the two fluids and across which the energy is transferred.
A non-corrugated plate heat exchanger that has flat plates with chemically etched flow passages which are diffusion bonded together into blocks.
A tubular heat exchanger in which a tube bundle is surrounded by a shell.
A reboiler often boils liquid coming from the bottom of a distillation column, after which the resulting vapour is returned to the distillation column.
A cylinder where the piston is actuated by compressed air.
A vessel intended to enable a chemical reaction process.
A vessel with a conical shape for filling or dosing purposes.
A column in which a gas mixture is contacted with a liquid for the purpose of preferentially dissolving one or more components of the gas mixture and to provide a solution of them in the liquid.
An electrical connector that is a fixed or free component that permits electrical connection(s) between two or more connectors where direct connection is mechanically impossible.
A physical fluid separator that is based on the principle of attraction exhibited by the surface of a solid for a liquid or a gas when they are in contact.
A circuit-breaker in which the contacts open and close in air at atmospheric pressure.
An electric generator for the production of alternating current and voltage.
An electric motor driven by alternating electric current.
A ball valve that is equipped with an actuator that manipulates a stream of fluid in the response to a signal from an external sensing element and with input of energy from an external source.
A rotary valve that has a ball closure member.
A valve that has one seat which provides a seal, and a bleeder line and valve that are tapped into the block valve's bonnet.
A butterfly valve that is equipped with an actuator that manipulates a stream of fluid in the response to a signal from an external sensing element and with input of energy from an external source.
A rotary valve that has a closure member of a disc type with a shaft parallel, or near parallel, to the plane of the disc, with an axis of rotation transverse to the flow direction.
A choke valve that is equipped with an actuator that manipulates a stream of fluid in the response to a signal from an external sensing element and with input of energy from an external source.
A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.
An analysing instrument that applies the principle of chromatography to analyse the molecular composition of a substance.
A pressure vessel with internal packing intended to effect the main stream by introducing counter flow of a regenerative liquid or gas. Dehydration of gas by use of glycol is a typical application.
A pressure relief valve that has its closing force provided by a spring.
A diaphragm valve that is equipped with an actuator that manipulates a stream of fluid in the response to a signal from an external sensing element and with input of energy from an external source.
A membrane valve that is a membrane valve where the closure member is a resilient diaphragm being forced against a port.
An electric generator for the production of direct current and voltage.
An electric motor for operation by direct current.
A process column intended to enable a distillation process.

A block and bleed valve that is incorporating two seats, each of which provides a seal, and a means of venting the space between the seats. The seats may isolate with the pressure differential acting in the same or in opposite directions depending on the design.
A power transformer of which the magnetic circuit and windings are not immersed in an insulating liquid.
A control valve that uses a rotating disc as closing element, and with a design that causes the disc to take a slightly eccentric path during actuation.
A valve that has a closing member which is an eccentric rotating disc.
An electrically controlled piping system that is situated within the frame and distributes purge gas inside the frame.
A heat exchanger that has finned tubes.
A flexible vertical or near vertical pipe for the flow of liquid or gas between the seabed and the surface.
A detecting instrument intended to measure and indicate flow rate and/or produce a signal which represents the measured flow rate.
ROV or diver-mateable flexible leads between subsea equipment items for chemical services.
ROV or diver-mateable flexible leads between subsea equipment items for electrical services.
ROV or diver-mateable flexible leads between subsea equipment items for hydraulic services.
ROV or diver-mateable flexible leads between subsea equipment items for optical services.
A chromatograph where gas is injected directly into one or more separation columns.
A chromatograph where a liquid sample is injected and evaporated and subsequently carried to one or more separation columns.
A circuit-breaker in which the arc develops in a blast of gas.
A control valve that is a gate valve and an actuated valve.
A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a gate or disc with a linear motion parallel, or nearly parallel, to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow.
A control valve that is a globe valve and an actuated valve.
A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat.
A separator that is based on the difference in specific gravity for the substances to be separated.
A hydraulically controlled piping system that is situated within the frame and distributes purge gas inside the frame.
A turbine in which liquid forces are driving the rotor by the reaction of acceleration of subject liquid flow in the runner while the pressure drops.
A detecting element intended to measure corrosion using electrical conductivity.
A switch which is operated by a person.
A valve not designed to regulate flow (e.g. on/off). A valve with multiple orifices or flow-restriction device to control fluid flow. Includes an actuator that needs auxiliary power to operate.

A valve not designed to regulate flow (e.g. on/off). A multi port valve which has the possibility of multiple distinct paths for flow through it. Includes an actuator that needs auxiliary power to operate.
A valve that has three or more ports arranged to switch flow.
A needle valve that is equipped with an actuator that manipulates a stream of fluid in the response to a signal from an external sensing element and with input of energy from an external source.
A globe valve that has a closure member with the shape of a conical plug (needle) which closes into a small seat.
A level transmitter that is producing a standardized electrical output signal based on the input signal from a nucleonic level detector.
A circuit-breaker in which the contacts open and close in oil.
An element designed to measure an oxidation reduction potential (ORP).
A pressure relief valve that uses a pilot valve to indirectly activate the main valve.
A lift check valve that has a free gravity or spring loaded piston type closure member.
A differential pressure flow meter utilizing a pitot tube (a probe with an open tip) that is inserted into the flow field.
A control valve that is also a plug valve and an actuated valve.
A rotary valve that has a quarter turn action in which the closure member is a cylindrical or tapered plug which operates by rotating on its axis and sealing against a downstream seat.
A pressure relief valve that is intended to release excess pressure or admit pressure to prevent a vacuum forming when filling or emptying a pipeline or tank.
A positive displacement pump which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.
A rigid vertical or near vertical pipe for the flow of liquid or gas between the seabed and the surface.

A positive displacement pump that consists of a chamber containing gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.
A slide valve that is equipped with an actuator that manipulates a stream of fluid in the response to a signal from an external sensing element and with input of energy from an external source.
A valve that opens and closes a passageway by sliding over a port.
A container intended for storage and/or processing of fluids. Relates to Spiral Plate Heat Exchanger.
A column which transforms a material from an unstable state to a more stable state; for fluids typically by removing volatile components from a mixture.
A distillation column intended to remove light components from a fluid.
An electrical connector capable of withstanding submersion to a specified depth.

A check valve that is a check valve where the closure member is a disc which swings freely on a hinge and which opens automatically when flow is established and closes automatically when flow ceases or is reversed.
A circuit-breaker in which the contacts open and close within a highly evacuated envelope.
A distillation column intended to withstand outside pressure.
A wafer pattern valve that is a check valve with a wafer pattern valve body.
A power transformer of which the magnetic circuit and windings are immersed in oil.
An enclosure that totally or partially surrounds an item in order to reduce its emitted noise.
A trap which, by a water seal, prevents foul air from rising from sinks, wash basins, drains, sewers etc.

A system or device mounted on radio masts, towers and other tall structures intended to assist navigators in determining their position or safe course, or to warn them of dangers or obstructions to navigation.
A large flat-bottomed boat that is built for carrying goods and people on rivers and canals or in harbours, with or without sails, towed by a tug or horse. Also a similar boat with its own engine.
A regulator ensuring constant volume in a HVAC system to reduce noise
A pipe coil in which heat is transferred from the material or space cooled to the primary refrigerant.
Structure to allow water or a pipeline to pass under a road/railway through a pipe or concrete tube. Typically if span greater than 12ft (3.7m) then structure is a bridge

A physical object intended to carry the load of equipment that is regularly lifted or launched, like a life boat, or of equipment that regularly is removed for inspection or maintenance, such as covers, hatches, etc.
A device that provides a safe and rapid method of descent in case of an emergency situation requiring evacuation.

A drain port is a collection port that can be installed in pressure sensing lines for transmitters, steam lines, etc. to be able to remove liquids from the system that otherwise would create problems for the instruments.
A 'liquid outlet port' that allows liquid to leave a container under gravity
A 'control panel' intended for electrical apparatus.
A artefact that is a an assembly of items required in the case of an emergency contained in a bag or some other container.
A heat exchanger that is intended to evaporate moisture or solvents in order to obtain a concentrate.
A pressure decrease device where the lower pressure is obtained by causing something to occupy or contain a larger space, or by acquiring greater volume.
An 'equipment class' that is a class of devices whose members can be used in a fitness centre.
A physical object that is intended to induce a reaction in a process fluid by heating it.
A personal H2S monitor is a device that detects the presence of hydrogen sulphide.
A fluid heater that is a coiled tube where heat is transferred from an internal heating medium to a surrounding substance.
A current limiter that limits the power (energy) which can be delivered from a safe area into a hazardous area.
A lagoon or aerated basin is a holding and/or treatment pond provided with artificial aeration to promote the biological oxidation of wastewaters.
A lifejacket is a type of personal flotation device designed to keep a persons airway clear of the water whether the wearer is conscious or unconscious.
An artefact that is intended to pass a line accurately and quickly.
A place which is a passage or a way of exit or entrance.
A vessel larger than a boat for transporting people or goods by sea
An 'equipment class' that is a class of devices engaged in meteorological observations.
A device that is capable of three-phase metering of liquid, oil and gas.
A gas flow damper that is able to stay in any position between fully open and fully closed.
An outfall is the discharge point of a waste stream into a body of water; alternatively it may be the outlet of a river, drain or a sewer where it discharges into the sea, a lake or the like.
A support-item that is the base or foot of a column or other upright structure.

A survival suit (or more specifically an immersion survival suit), is a special type of waterproof dry suit that protects the wearer from hypothermia from immersion in cold water, after abandoning a sinking or capsized vessel, especially in the open ocean
A personal radiation monitor is a device that detects the presence of any radiation sources.

A recuperator is a special purpose counter-flow energy recovery heat exchanger positioned within the supply and exhaust air streams of an air handling system, or in the exhaust gases of an industrial process, in order to recover the waste heat.
A process control unit that can be operated in remote.
A machine used to compact soil, gravel, concrete, or asphalt in the construction of roads and foundations
A machine that cleans the road
A 'well drilling system' and an 'artefact' in which the torque is transferred to the drill string using rotary table and kelly.
An information object that indicates the location of safety signs and other relevant safety information.
An information object with a symbol representing some hazard or safety information.
A connection point intended for collection of samples

A physical object that consists of wedge-shaped pieces of metal loosely joined together and fitted into a bushing to support a string of pipe. The slips have gripping elements to prevent the pipe from slipping down the drilling hole.
Pipework/channel/scupper designed to flow storm water (i.e. arising from atmospheric precipitation) from source areas on site to a discharge or outflow point (excludes drainage from bunded area)
